<br>
My hedgehog story is kind of sad. I think it was like my 17th birthday present from my mom, we went to the pet store, picked out this awesomely friendly female and had the pet store tag her with some paint so I could pick her up the next day (after making sure dad was okay with it). Came back the next day and THEY HAD SOLD MY HEDGEHOG that was already paid for! WTF! The one they replaced her with was an evil male who was very unhappy all of the time and no matter how hard I tried to coax him into a happier mood, it never worked. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.mywhimsy.com/boards/dvicons/sad.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I love animals, but I could never handle him without leather gloves, and well...I like animals I can interact with. I couldn't keep him, and he went to a friend of mine who wasn't unhappy to keep him in his cage most of the time and have an untouchable pet.<br>
